app.containers.BookingPage.insurancePoli:
If you cancel the purchase of car insurance provided by our company, please bring your own car insurance when you pick up the car. According to the US government regulations, cars without purchased insurance are prohibited from driving on the road. Please choose according to the actual situation.
Rental Car Insurance including Liability Insurance Supplement(LIS), Collision Damage Waiver(CDW), and Personal Accident Insurance (PAI)
1.Liability Insurance Supplement(LIS) or Supplemental Liability Insurance(SLI) typically covers damages to other people’s property (e.g. other people’s cars) as well as medical costs for injuries when you are at fault in a crash. In most states, it required minimum levels of liability insurance to drive. If you have your own automobile insurance policy with coverage above the minimum amounts, your policy might cover by your insurance package. You need to contact your insurance agent to verify the policy and coverage you have.
2.Collision Damage Waiver(CDW) indicates the car rental company will waive all or part of its cost if the rental car is damaged or stolen by authorized driver. Collision Damage Waiver normally includes Loss Damage Waiver (LDW), means the coverage of your property loss in your car. From above, CDW covers the main part of situation you may face when you rent a car.

For the customer who has your primary auto insurance, you may already have CDW for a rental car as part of your primary auto insurance. Please check with your primary auto insurance policy and your insurance agent.
Besides, most premium credit cards, such as Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Discover, especially gold or platinum cards, provide this coverage, with certain limitations, as a benefit of using the credit card to rent cars. However, some cards do not provide this benefit for luxury cars, SUVs, and Vans.
Most U.S. credit cards come with CDW benefit called secondary auto rental insurance. It waives the renter’s responsibility to pay for damages to the rental vehicle but doesn’t cover administrative fees or total loss of your rental car after an accident. A select group of cards offers primary rental car insurance, which takes the coverage provided a step further. These cards benefit not only cover the amount beyond what your own insurance covers, but also cover the loss of the rental vehicle. For the CDW benefit of the credit card, you may contact your credit card provider.

3.Personal Accident Insurance (PAI) includes medical, ambulance and death benefits for you (the rental car driver) and your passenger, while LIS covering other people’s property damage and injuries in an accident. For the most common situation, the benefits provided by PAI are covered in your health, life or auto insurance policy. Also, you should know PAI included Personal Effects Coverage (PEC), which covers the theft of possessions from the rental car.
